The paper deals with the convergence of the sum-product algorithm, which is a widely used algorithm in artificial intelligence and machine learning for probabilistic inference in graphical models. Therefore, cs.AI and cs.LG are the most likely categories. The paper also involves computational complexity and optimization, which are relevant to cs.DS. The use of information theory and message passing algorithms suggests cs.IT and cs.SI as possible categories.
